properties.name: Northolt Park
properties.wheelchair:description: Flat access to both platforms. Please note that there is no flat access between platforms (access between platforms is via the footbridge). Flat access from one platform to another is via public footpaths and is a distance of roughly 500m.

properties.name: Reedham
properties.wheelchair:description: Level access to platform 2 (to Tattenham Corner). Steps to platform 1 (to London).

properties.name: Hendon
properties.wheelchair:description: Step-free southbound only. Access from platform to train by manual boarding ramp.

properties.name: Waddon
properties.wheelchair:description: Step-free access via side gate to platform 2 (to Sutton). Steps to platform 1 (to London).

properties.name: East Croydon
properties.wheelchair:description: Lifts from West entrance & ramps from main George Street concourse to all platforms. Accessible WCs not checked today.

properties.name: Strawberry Hill
properties.wheelchair:description: Ramp at approx 1:14 gradient to Platform 1. Short unevenly-graded floor at approx 1:10 gradient to Platform 2. Step-free access between platforms via full-barrier level crossing.

properties.name: Kidbrooke
properties.wheelchair:description: Step free access to both platforms. For trains to London from platform 1 via Park Terrace, for trains away from London from Platform 2 via Henley Cross, step free interchange between platforms via road bridge is in excess of 300 metres.

properties.name: Hampton
properties.note: Platform 1 is Clapham Junction and London Waterloo bound; Platform 2 is Shepperton bound
properties.wheelchair:description: Level access to both platforms from separate entrances. Step-free access between platforms via street and level crossing approximately 230m.

properties.name: Welling
properties.wheelchair:description: Step free access to Platform 1 for services towards London via main entrance. Step free access to Platform 2 for services away from London via side entrance on Car Park. Step free interchange between platforms via the street 300 metres.

properties.name: Barnehurst
properties.wheelchair:description: Step free access to platform 1 for services to London via path from ticket office. Step free access to platform 2 for services away from London via car park.No step free interchange between platforms.

properties.name: Erith
properties.wheelchair:description: Step free access to platform 2 for services away from London. There is no step free access to Platform 1. No step free interchange between platforms.

properties.name: Streatham
properties.wheelchair:description: Step-free southbound only. Access from platform to train by manual boarding ramp.

properties.name: Sutton
properties.wheelchair:description: Lifts to all platforms. Accessible toilets on Platforms 1 & 2/3. Also ChangingPlaces Toilet on 2/3. http://changingplaces.uktoiletmap.org/toilet/view/620 - Station supervisor is able to offer a key to non-travellers.

properties.name: Barnes
properties.wheelchair:description: Level access to Platforms 1 and 4 from separate entrances. Steps to Platforms 2/3.

properties.name: Haydons Road
properties.wheelchair:description: Access from platform to train by manual boarding ramp.

properties.name: Wandsworth Common
properties.wheelchair:description: Level access to platform 1 (to Croydon / London Bridge) via rear entrance. Steps to all other platforms.

properties.name: London Victoria
properties.wheelchair:description: Concourse to platforms step-free & wide gates. Access to all trains by portable ramps, no Harrington Humps discovered yet.

properties.name: Bexley
properties.wheelchair:description: Only the near platform (to Crayford) is accessible

properties.name: Balham
properties.wheelchair:description: Access from platform to train by manual boarding ramp.

properties.name: London Bridge
properties.wheelchair:description: Step-free access street to train

properties.name: St Margarets
properties.wheelchair:description: Step free access for trains towards Twickenham and Strawberry Hill. Steps required for trains towards Richmond. Access for Amyand Road for Platform 3 only.

properties.name: Hadley Wood
properties.wheelchair:description: Step free access to/from platform 4 only (Northbound) via a moderate slope. Customers travelling towards London who require step-free access may use your ticket to travel north to Potters Bar station before catching a train towards London.

properties.name: Blackheath
properties.wheelchair:description: Step free access to platform 1 for services towards London via lift. Step free access to platform 2 for services away from London via ramp from side entrance. Step free interchange via front of station. Step access to both platforms via booking hall.

properties.name: Raynes Park
properties.wheelchair:description: This station has step-free access to Platforms 1 and 2 (for trains towards London Waterloo) via long and steep ramps at up to 1:10 gradient. There is no step-free access to Platforms 3 and 4 (for trains towards Chessington South/ Kingston/ Surbiton).

properties.name: Carshalton
properties.wheelchair:description: Access from platform to train by manual boarding ramp

properties.name: Westcombe Park
properties.wheelchair:description: Access from platform to train by manual boarding ramp.

properties.name: Woolwich Dockyard
properties.wheelchair:description: Step free access to platform for services away from London. There is no step free access to Platform 1. No step free interchange between platforms.

properties.name: Woolwich Arsenal
properties.wheelchair:description: Access from platform to train by manual boarding ramp.

properties.name: Slade Green
properties.wheelchair:description: Access from platform to train by manual boarding ramp.

properties.name: Elmstead Woods
properties.wheelchair:description: Step free access to platform 4 for services away from London from Station Approach. There is no step free access to Platform 1, 2 or 3. No step free interchange between platforms.

properties.name: Chislehurst
properties.wheelchair:description: Step free access to platform 4 for services away from London. There is no step free access to Platform 1 2 or 3.

properties.name: Chelsfield
properties.wheelchair:description: Step free access to platform 1 from Station Approach Rd. Steep ramp to access Platform 2 from Warren Road. Step free interchange via road and steep paths is in excess of 400metres.

properties.name: Sanderstead
properties.wheelchair:description: Level access to both platforms via separate entrances. Long access route between platforms via street, steep in places (over 400m and gradient above 1:10).

properties.name: Riddlesdown
properties.wheelchair:description: Step-free access to platforms via long and steep ramps (over 1:10 gradient).

properties.name: Lower Sydenham
properties.wheelchair:description: Step Free to both platforms, No step free interchange between platforms.

properties.name: New Beckenham
properties.wheelchair:description: Step free access to both platforms. No step free interchange between platforms.

properties.name: Clock House
properties.wheelchair:description: Step free access to platform 2 for services away from London via Clock House Road. There is no step free access to Platform 1.

properties.name: Eden Park
properties.wheelchair:description: Step free access to platform 1 for services to London. There is no step free access to Platform 2.Only step access to platform 2 for services away from London. No step free interchange between platforms.

properties.name: Chiswick
properties.wheelchair:description: Level access to Platform 1 (for trains towards London Waterloo). Short ramp at approx 1:7 gradient to Platform 2 (for trains towards Hounslow) via separate entrance. No reasonable step-free access between platforms.

properties.name: Hounslow
properties.wheelchair:description: Steps or ramp (approx. gradient 1:15) to Platform 1 (trains towards Chiswick). Level access to Platform 2 from separate entrance. Access between platforms via footbridge with steps, or step-free route via street approximately 150m.

properties.name: Norbiton
properties.source:name: local knowledge
properties.wheelchair:description: There is step free access via ramps to both platforms. Interchange via a stepped subway.

properties.name: Teddington
properties.source:name: local knowledge
properties.wheelchair:description: Level access to both platforms from street but bridge between platforms not wheelchair accessible.

properties.name: Hackbridge
properties.wheelchair:description: Access from platform to train by manual boarding ramp

properties.name: Mitcham Junction
properties.wheelchair:description: Access from platform to train by manual boarding ramp.

properties.name: West Hampstead Thameslink
properties.wheelchair:description: Access from platform to train by manual boarding ramp.

properties.name: Penge East
properties.wheelchair:description: Step free access to platform 1 from main entrance. Step free access to platform 2 via Lindon Grove - No step free interchange between platforms but stepped access via station footbridge is available.

properties.name: Bromley South
properties.wheelchair:description: Access from platform to train by manual boarding ramp

properties.name: Crofton Park
properties.wheelchair:description: Step-free platform interchange requires a 400m+ journey via street. Access from platform to train by manual boarding ramp.

properties.name: Beckenham Hill
properties.wheelchair:description: Step-free platform interchange requires a 400m+ journey via street. Access from platform to train by manual boarding ramp.

properties.name: Ravensbourne
properties.wheelchair:description: Step-free southbound only. Access from platform to train by manual boarding ramp.

properties.name: Norbury
properties.wheelchair:description: Step-free access to all platforms via long and steep ramps (over 400m long and above 1:10 gradient).

properties.name: Mottingham
properties.wheelchair:description: Step free access to Platform 1 for services to London via main station entrance. Step free access to platform 2 for services away from London via side entrance. No step free interchange between platforms.

properties.name: Sidcup
properties.wheelchair:description: Entrance depends on which platform you need to access, only the London bound platform is accessible from the station building itself, the other platform is accessed via a separate entrance on the far side

properties.name: Cricklewood
properties.wheelchair:description: You can only enter and exit southbound platform. Access from platform to train by manual boarding ramp.

properties.name: Waterloo East
properties.wheelchair:description: Step free access to Waterloo East is only through use of lift at Waterloo Main. Ramps access to the platforms is steep.

properties.name: Hayes
properties.wheelchair:description: Short ramp access from car park to station entrance. Step free access to these terminal platform from station entrance via short steep ramp.

properties.name: Maze Hill
properties.wheelchair:description: Access from platform to train by manual boarding ramp.

properties.name: Belvedere
properties.wheelchair:description: Step free access to both platforms. No step free interchange between platforms which is via a footbridge.

properties.name: Coulsdon South
properties.wheelchair:description: Access from platform to train by manual boarding ramp

properties.name: Charlton
properties.wheelchair:description: Access from platform to train by manual boarding ramp

properties.description: This station is served every 2 hours, Monday-Friday in the peak direction only.
properties.name: Sudbury & Harrow Road
Sundridge Park
properties.wheelchair:description: Step free access available to platform 2 for services to Bromley North via gate from side path. There is no step free access to Platform 1.

properties.name: East Dulwich
properties.wheelchair:description: Steep ramp to platform 1 (to London Bridge). Steep ramp to platform 2 (to Tulse Hill). Ramps are longer than 400m/above 1:10 gradient).

properties.name: South Greenford
properties.wheelchair:description: This station has a degree of step free access to both platforms however this is via Long ramps to both palforms (approx 1:10).
